The Rocket Launcher is a very powerful primary weapon. It can be used in all ranges. At close range, shoot it at an incoming enemy for a lot of damage. Most classes die with 2 rockets. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-3.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/c1/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-3.jpg/aid361495-v4-728px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Shoot it at an enemy's feet! An enemy is less likely to dodge a rocket attack if you shoot it at their feet. Keep this in mind, especially at close range. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-4.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/7f/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-4.jpg/aid361495-v4-728px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

At medium range, shoot it at an enemy for a very strong attack. At this range you can finish most classes with 3 rockets. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/dd/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-5.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/dd/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-5.jpg/aid361495-v4-728px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

At long range, shoot it at an enemy for a shot that can deal much damage to your enemy if it hits directly. Remember that it helps to try to predict an enemy's movement before shooting because it can be easily dodged. Use your rocket against enemy snipers. While, as said before, they can dodge quickly, the rockets deal a surprising amount of splash damage. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b5/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-6.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-6.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b5/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-6.jpg/aid361495-v4-728px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Watch out! You can injure or kill yourself with your own rocket shots! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9f/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-7.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-7.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/9f/Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-7.jpg/aid361495-v4-728px-Play-a-Soldier-in-Team-Fortress-2-Step-7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"455","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
